history.content: The best preparation is to just go through the course from previous semesters.

children.subject:
I wish I recapped 61B's data structures and algorithms before I took CS 170 and CS 188. Also, CS 70 proofs/graphs are helpful for CS 170. 

Acc. to Prof Sahai, taking CS 188 without EE 126 is like walking through a garden and only noticing the flowers while there's a dragon sitting in the field in front of you. I took 188 before 126, but after studying 126, what he said makes a lot of sense. Wouldn't hurt to postpone 188 by 1 semester if you are planning on taking 126 at some point.

61B is only really helpful for the first part of the class which covers graph algorithms like dfs, bfs, A* search. The course does reteach these though. You should probably be familiar with data structures in general though, like trees, queues, stacks. The most important part is the probability aspect, so you should have a mastery of stat 140 material.
I see, thanks! Would you recommend watching Josh Hug's lecture as well as doing assignment, hw from past semesters to get ahead? I do not want to bet overwhelmed in the first part of 188...
Is it possible to take CS 188 without CS 61b? I am not a CS major, and have taken 61a, data 100 and Stat 140.
